# Woflang 7 (Modularized, Refactored, Restored)

Woflang is a stack-based, extensible, and mischievous programming language.

## Building

- C++17 or newer (C++23 best)
- Windows: MSYS2/MinGW or Visual Studio
- Linux/macOS: GCC/Clang

```
mkdir build
cd build
cmake ..
cmake --build . --config Release
```

## Directory Layout

- `src/core/` — Interpreter, plugin system, ops
- `src/io/`   — Tokenizer and IO helpers
- `src/plugins/` — Plugins, including sample eggs/curses
- `main.cpp` — REPL CLI entry

## Features

- Modular op registration (`register_op`)
- Dynamic plugin loading (.dll/.so)
- "Curse" and "easter egg" commands (try: `wof> cursed`, `wof> egg`)
- Plugins in `src/plugins/`, loaded at runtime
- All quirks/hidden features restored

## Plugin API

1. Export `extern "C" void init_plugin(OpTable*)`.
2. Register ops on the interpreter's table.

Example plugin source in `src/plugins/sample_plugin.cpp`.

